revision.text:
'''List of ЕҢhechi ЕҢji Shrines''' is a list of shrines along the {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|зҶҠйҮҺеҸӨйҒ“}} ЕҢhechi route that bear the name "ЕҢji."
These shrines are distinct from the ЕҢji shrines along the {{ill|Kii Route|ja|зҙҖдјҠи·Ҝ}} and {{ill|Nakahechi|ja|дёӯиҫәи·Ҝ}} in terms of their establishment periods and circumstances. As a result, they are not included in the {{ill|Kumano Ninety-Nine ЕҢji Shrines|ja|зҶҠйҮҺд№қеҚҒд№қзҺӢеӯҗзӨҫ}}. See also {{ill|Kumano Ninety-Nine ЕҢji Shrines|ja|д№қеҚҒд№қзҺӢеӯҗ}}.
* {{ill|Wakaichi ЕҢji Gongen Monument|ja|иӢҘдёҖзҺӢеӯҗжЁ©зҸҫзў‘}} (Wakaichi ЕҢji Ruins) * {{ill|Susami ЕҢji Shrine|ja|е‘ЁеҸӮиҰӢзҺӢеӯҗзҘһзӨҫ}} (Wakaichi ЕҢji Gongen Shrine) * {{ill|Wabukigawa ЕҢji Shrine|ja|е’Ңж·ұе·қзҺӢеӯҗзҘһзӨҫ}}
== References == * Edited by {{ill|Ise Culture Publishing|ja|дјҠеӢўж–ҮеҢ–иҲҺ}}, *Sacred Pilgrimage: Kumano, Yoshino, Mount Koya, and the Pilgrimage Routes,* Ise Culture Publishing. * Supervised by {{ill|Toshikatsu Ue|ja|е®Үжұҹж•ҸеӢқ}}, 2004, *Walking the Kumano Kodo,* Yama-kei Publishers, ISBN 4635600335. * Kinan Culture Research Association, 2001, *Survey Report on the Kumano Kodo ЕҢhechi: From Tanabe City to Kushimoto Town,* Wakayama Prefecture Nishimuro Promotion Bureau.
== See Also == * {{ill|ЕҢhechi|ja|еӨ§иҫәи·Ҝ}} * {{ill|Kumano Ninety-Nine ЕҢji Shrines|ja|д№қеҚҒд№қзҺӢеӯҗ}}
{{Shinto Horizontal}} [[Category:Shrines in Wakayama Prefecture]] [[Category:Kumano faith]] [[Category:Lists of shrines]] [[ja:еӨ§иҫәи·ҜгҒ®зҺӢеӯҗзӨҫдёҖиҰ§]]

