'''List of ЕҢhechi ЕҢji Shrines''' is a list of shrines along the {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|зҶҠйҮҺеҸӨйҒ“|12=draft}} ЕҢhechi route that bear the name "ЕҢji." 

These shrines are distinct from the ЕҢji shrines along the {{ill|Kii Route|ja|зҙҖдјҠи·Ҝ|12=draft}} and {{ill|Nakahechi|ja|дёӯиҫәи·Ҝ|12=draft}} in terms of their establishment periods and circumstances. As a result, they are not included in the {{ill|Kumano Ninety-Nine ЕҢji Shrines|ja|зҶҠйҮҺд№қеҚҒд№қзҺӢеӯҗзӨҫ|12=draft}}. See also {{ill|Kumano Ninety-Nine ЕҢji Shrines|ja|д№қеҚҒд№қзҺӢеӯҗ|1=KujЕ«ku ЕҢji|2=ja|3=д№қеҚҒд№қзҺӢеӯҗ|4=fr|5=KujЕ«kuЕҚji|1=KujЕ«ku ЕҢji|1=KujЕ«ku ЕҢji|12=draft}}.

* {{ill|Wakaichi ЕҢji Gongen Monument|ja|иӢҘдёҖзҺӢеӯҗжЁ©зҸҫзў‘|12=draft}} (Wakaichi ЕҢji Ruins)
* {{ill|Susami ЕҢji Shrine|ja|е‘ЁеҸӮиҰӢзҺӢеӯҗзҘһзӨҫ|1=Susami-ЕҚji Shrine|12=draft}} (Wakaichi ЕҢji Gongen Shrine)
